<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetConsole" Title="LogTargetConsole class" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    LogTargetConsole
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Declaration">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[class LogTargetConsole : public ILogTarget;]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>LogTargetConsole</TypeRef> class is a Windows console <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogTarget">ILogTarget</PageRef> implementation. It writes messages to the attached console and changes the console text colour based on message severity.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      This target is compiled only when the <TypeRef>INCLUDE_LOGTARGETCONSOLE</TypeRef> preprocessor symbol is enabled. It opens the attached console through <TypeRef>CONOUT$</TypeRef> rather than assuming the standard output handle is a console.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        Call <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetConsole.OpenConsoleHandle">OpenConsoleHandle</PageRef> before expecting messages to appear. If no console handle is open, <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetConsole.LogMessage">LogMessage</PageRef> returns without writing output.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
